==English==
=== Etymology ===
Written form of a [[w:reduction (linguistics)|reduction]] of "[[got]] [[you]]"

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-gotcha.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Predicate phrase===
[[Category:English language]]
'''gotcha'''
#(''colloquial'') got you; have you; understand, comprehend
#:''I '''gotcha'''.''

===Noun===
'''gotcha'''
#(''colloquial'') A potential [[problem]] or source of [[trouble]].
#:''Review the work thoroughly and make sure there are no '''gotchas'''.''

